WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:31.600 --> 01:35.485
I sell mayhem, scandal, murder, and doom.

01:35.560 --> 01:38.525
Oh, Jesus, I do.

01:38.600 --> 01:41.365
I sell the newborn and the dead.

01:41.440 --> 01:46.128
I sell the wretched, magnificent city
of New York back to its people.

01:48.120 --> 01:50.043
I sell newspapers.

02:01.920 --> 02:04.161
Thanks for your time. Yeah?

02:04.240 --> 02:06.322
Porter. I got a shooting, plus a fire.

02:06.400 --> 02:09.722
- Mm. Any bodies?
- At least two, Projects on Avenue D.

02:09.800 --> 02:11.205
Paul said something about a kid.

02:11.280 --> 02:13.647
I'm on it. I'm on it. Thanks.

02:15.280 --> 02:19.445
I'm always running to the place
where the bad thing just happened,

02:19.520 --> 02:21.841
arriving just after the danger has passed,

02:21.920 --> 02:25.805
watching from a safe distance,
searching for an angle,

02:25.880 --> 02:28.042
that little wrinkle, the kick to the heart

02:28.160 --> 02:31.802
that makes you want to put down
the dollar and pick up the paper.

02:31.920 --> 02:35.887
With three deadlines a week,
I'm always looking for a good story.

02:36.560 --> 02:39.484
I seen the smoke,
and I'm looking up there.

02:39.560 --> 02:42.843
And that's when Demetrius,
he come jumping through that window.

02:42.920 --> 02:46.402
And he on fire, burning like all over.

02:46.520 --> 02:48.805
And he holding Vernon here.

02:48.880 --> 02:52.725
And Demetrius, he fall, fall, and fall.

02:52.800 --> 02:55.925
I can see he gonna land
on top of the baby.

02:56.000 --> 03:00.005
And then just before Demetrius land,
he do this little kind of flip.

03:00.080 --> 03:02.162
And he landed on his back.

03:02.240 --> 03:04.971
And he holding the baby up, like...

03:05.080 --> 03:07.924
And I can see that he do that on purpose.

03:08.040 --> 03:10.245
What did you do?

03:10.320 --> 03:13.210
I run over and I pick up Vernon here.

03:16.080 --> 03:17.844
And I see Demetrius.

03:19.040 --> 03:22.923
He just not gonna make it,
because he landed on his back like that.

03:23.000 --> 03:25.002
Hey, little man.

03:27.040 --> 03:30.725
I'm sorry that happened to you
and your daddy. You okay?

03:30.800 --> 03:32.325
No, no, no, he don't talk yet.

03:32.440 --> 03:35.364
Fall, fall, fall.

03:48.160 --> 03:50.003
Thanks for your time.

03:50.080 --> 03:54.244
Hey, you're the one that helped
them find that little girl?

03:59.040 --> 04:01.845
I write a column for a daily newspaper.

04:01.920 --> 04:05.481
In other words, I'm an endangered species.

04:05.560 --> 04:08.564
I used to think my stories
could make a difference.

04:08.640 --> 04:12.525
Now I just hope they are
enough to feed my family.

04:12.600 --> 04:17.562
These days, eight million kids have
iPhones and post their videos on YouTube

04:17.640 --> 04:21.005
like they're actually reporting
and commenting on something.

04:21.079 --> 04:23.965
My wife says I sound old.

04:24.040 --> 04:27.522
I'm heading into a long one,
so you'll probably get home before me.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.405
Josephine needs to get paid.

04:29.480 --> 04:31.765
And please remember to scrub
the pots and pans.

04:31.840 --> 04:33.125
You keep leaving them for me.

04:33.200 --> 04:34.850
Yeah, well, they have to soak overnight.

04:34.960 --> 04:36.564
Oh, yeah?

04:36.640 --> 04:38.165
- Yeah.
- Really?

04:38.280 --> 04:39.725
Is that what your mother told you?

04:39.840 --> 04:41.001
Well, look, I got to go, baby.

04:41.080 --> 04:42.320
- Wait, Porter.
- What?

04:42.400 --> 04:44.129
Did you remember your tuxedo?

04:45.280 --> 04:47.325
Yeah, but I don't want to go.

04:47.400 --> 04:50.125
Everyone's going to be
sucking up to Hobbs...

04:50.200 --> 04:53.926
You know, if they're really thinking about
cutting your column, you better go.

05:47.360 --> 05:51.604
I know you are a watcher,
Mr. Wren, but it is rude to stare.

05:51.680 --> 05:56.365
I'm sorry. I was just trying
to figure out where I knew you from.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.005
I see you recognize me, though.

05:58.080 --> 05:59.684
From your cheesy picture.

05:59.760 --> 06:02.684
The one that goes with my column.

06:02.760 --> 06:06.045
Your smug expression is annoying.

06:06.120 --> 06:09.005
It was taken last year,

06:09.080 --> 06:11.445
in the waning moments of my youth.

06:11.520 --> 06:13.204
Right before they retired the film camera?

06:13.280 --> 06:15.965
- Wow.
- Sorry.

06:16.040 --> 06:18.725
Does anyone actually read
the newspaper anymore?

06:18.800 --> 06:20.605
Well, I have a few fans
of the print edition.

06:20.680 --> 06:24.445
I'm told they Twitter at me.

06:24.520 --> 06:26.522
I think they Twitter
about how awesome it is,

06:26.600 --> 06:30.445
the feel of the paper,
the smell of the ink.

06:30.520 --> 06:32.409
Hashtag-well-written-column.

06:34.160 --> 06:38.484
Well... I do like the feel of the paper.

06:38.560 --> 06:41.803
And your column, Mr. Wren,
is always very well written,

06:41.920 --> 06:44.287
in an old-time, classic kind of way.

06:47.440 --> 06:49.245
- Well...
- I do wonder, though.

06:49.320 --> 06:52.765
It must be depressing for you
to be in all those places

06:52.840 --> 06:54.604
right after a terrible thing has happened.

06:54.680 --> 06:56.165
You must have seen so many awful things.

06:56.240 --> 06:58.402
I've seen a few things.

07:00.040 --> 07:02.245
People seem to open up to you.

07:02.320 --> 07:05.365
You must have a skill for
asking the right questions.

07:05.440 --> 07:10.281
Usually people want to tell somebody,
and I'm just there at the right time.

07:10.360 --> 07:12.328
Come on. You're being modest.

07:13.840 --> 07:15.365
What brings you to the party?

07:16.680 --> 07:20.722
My boyfriend, Charlie's bank,
does some kind of business with the company

07:20.800 --> 07:22.564
that I guess just bought your paper.

07:24.160 --> 07:26.525
You all work for Hobbs now, I guess.

07:26.600 --> 07:29.365
"All" meaning mankind? Yes.

07:33.640 --> 07:36.325
You grateful you landed a job
that pays you to stare at people?

07:39.440 --> 07:41.329
Look...

07:42.520 --> 07:44.645
I deal with bullshitters all day.

07:44.720 --> 07:49.605
But I'm on my own time here,
so, if this is all going somewhere,

07:49.680 --> 07:51.250
get to it already.

07:53.200 --> 07:55.965
Well, it's complicated.
It takes some time to explain.

07:56.040 --> 07:57.883
Oh.

07:57.960 --> 08:00.281
Could we leave right now
and go back to my apartment?

08:00.360 --> 08:03.325
It's only 15 blocks from here.

08:03.400 --> 08:05.562
Charlie wouldn't be coming.

08:07.880 --> 08:09.848
Is this about your husband's death?

08:11.000 --> 08:12.565
Porter Wren, is it?

08:12.640 --> 08:13.685
Yes.

08:13.760 --> 08:15.922
You must come and have
a word with Mr. Hobbs.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.764
He's quite eager to meet you.

08:19.360 --> 08:21.010
Excuse me.

08:31.960 --> 08:36.525
This is Porter Wren, the investigative
reporter who found the girl.

08:39.440 --> 08:40.965
Excuse me, Mr. Hobbs?

08:41.080 --> 08:46.402
Mr. Porter Wren, sir, famed investigative
reporter who now writes the column.

08:46.520 --> 08:47.965
Really?

08:48.040 --> 08:49.325
Yeah?

08:49.400 --> 08:50.965
I really think this could happen.

08:51.040 --> 08:52.371
I think it's very prudent.

08:53.840 --> 08:56.047
Every single...

08:59.400 --> 09:01.801
Wonderful.

09:16.760 --> 09:19.161
The invitation still stands?

09:20.000 --> 09:21.764
Yes.

10:11.320 --> 10:12.890
Come in.

10:15.960 --> 10:17.962
I want to show you this.

10:20.400 --> 10:22.004
Okay, this is what we're talking about.

10:22.080 --> 10:24.365
This is where we start.

10:24.440 --> 10:26.920
- This is where we start?
- Yes.

10:27.000 --> 10:29.446
- Another drink?
- Why not?

10:57.920 --> 11:00.526
To help you through the gates of hell.

11:02.240 --> 11:04.163
This is a police report.

11:16.880 --> 11:19.042
It's a bit stingy with the tonic and ice.

11:19.120 --> 11:23.525
Well, I want you drunk, so I can
tell whether you are a lout or not.

11:23.600 --> 11:26.001
You know you can get in a lot
of trouble for having these files?

11:27.920 --> 11:30.161
Detectives don't even let other
cops see these things.

11:31.600 --> 11:33.443
I know that.

11:33.520 --> 11:38.682
Okay. So, Simon Crowley was found
in the rubble of a demolished building.

11:38.800 --> 11:42.964
Surrounding the body were
small pieces of jade.

11:44.640 --> 11:48.162
Police have no idea how he got in there,
given the high fence with wire,

11:48.240 --> 11:51.847
nor can they determine the cause
of death because of the...

11:52.960 --> 11:55.565
The bulldozers
and the rats. You can say it.

11:55.640 --> 11:58.849
I've read the report 17 times.

12:01.120 --> 12:02.326
I'm sorry.

12:07.160 --> 12:09.322
"The world-famous filmmaker
appears incapable of smiling."

12:12.560 --> 12:14.403
Clearly.
"Several hours into the interview...

12:15.560 --> 12:17.685
I came to realize that Simon Crowley..."

12:17.760 --> 12:19.645
Thank you.

12:19.720 --> 12:24.965
"...is not a nice person, particularly,
and he doesn't care if you know it.

12:25.040 --> 12:29.725
In his pursuit of great movies,
woman upon woman, and cigarettes,

12:29.800 --> 12:32.883
in that order, niceness is irrelevant."

12:35.160 --> 12:37.003
Mixed review.

12:40.960 --> 12:44.681
- Is that Best Director?
- Best Original Screenplay.

12:44.760 --> 12:45.761
Apparently it's what they give you

12:45.840 --> 12:48.605
when they want to give you
Best Director but they can't.

12:48.680 --> 12:50.364
VANTAGES

12:50.440 --> 12:52.124
FILMMAKER CROWLEY FOUND DEAD

12:52.200 --> 12:54.245
They still can't figure out
how he got in there.

12:54.320 --> 12:57.369
The place was all locked up and
he didn't have a key on him.

13:00.600 --> 13:03.649
What's the story with the pieces of jade?

13:03.800 --> 13:05.404
No idea.

13:41.120 --> 13:43.282
Could I have my coat, please?

13:45.080 --> 13:48.004
I hope you don't feel like
I've wasted your time.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.531
Here's my number.

14:12.160 --> 14:15.881
When the gate shuts, my work and the city

14:16.000 --> 14:19.800
remain on the other side of the wall
that surrounds our hidden home.

14:19.920 --> 14:24.403
Lisa and I fell in love with this house
when we were first married.

14:24.480 --> 14:29.122
There's something about it surviving
hundreds of years, like a secret.

14:29.200 --> 14:30.440
It kept me honest.

14:32.520 --> 14:35.364
Anywhere else, this house
should be mundane.

14:35.440 --> 14:39.923
But in Manhattan, it was a miracle.

14:40.000 --> 14:44.845
My family slept inside, safe from
the dangers of these dark streets,

14:44.920 --> 14:49.605
secluded too from the world of Caroline
Crowley and her famous dead husband,

14:49.680 --> 14:52.285
who could not enter this sacred place,

14:52.360 --> 14:56.524
unless, of course, I brought
them home with me.

14:57.040 --> 14:58.445
Did you redo it yesterday?

14:58.520 --> 15:00.602
- It happened too late.
- Daddy-bird!

15:00.680 --> 15:02.045
Saved the wedding dress part just for you.

15:02.120 --> 15:03.325
All right. I'm on it.

15:03.400 --> 15:04.765
I'm on it. Thanks.

15:06.560 --> 15:08.642
Classy quote from the gymnastics coach.

15:09.480 --> 15:11.608
You see what they put for the headline?

15:15.280 --> 15:18.325
- The Pulitzer is waiting.
- I liked it.

15:18.400 --> 15:20.482
You okay?

15:20.560 --> 15:23.040
Yeah, I'll be all right in a few hours.

15:23.120 --> 15:24.445
You didn't drive home last night, did you?

15:24.520 --> 15:27.490
No. I left the car in the lot.

15:28.760 --> 15:30.485
Oh. Excuse me.

15:30.560 --> 15:34.201
- Sally, come. We need to get dressed.
- Oh, no, but I...

15:34.280 --> 15:36.282
- Tommy, let's go.
- Never!

15:36.360 --> 15:37.645
- Morning, Josephine.
- Tommy?

15:37.720 --> 15:40.121
- I don't wanna come.
- Tommy.

15:40.200 --> 15:42.680
Tommy. Don't you kick me.

15:44.880 --> 15:47.724
- Yes. I got him.
- Pick him up.

15:47.840 --> 15:49.405
There you go.

15:49.480 --> 15:51.365
You better come on with me.

15:51.440 --> 15:53.363
- Get your tush under control.
- Come on here.

15:53.440 --> 15:56.444
Josephine, if you could pick up
the house a bit today, it'd be great.

15:56.520 --> 16:00.685
Like, maybe you could do, like, the dishes,
or maybe do the pots in the sink?

16:00.760 --> 16:03.525
You know, she ignores me all the time.

16:03.600 --> 16:07.207
Oh, listen. I have an important surgery
that I have to do tomorrow night,

16:07.320 --> 16:11.484
so I won't be able to go to that
dinner with Lorca and Cabot.

16:11.560 --> 16:13.324
Well, I'm not going without you.

16:13.400 --> 16:15.641
We've rescheduled that, like, four times.

16:15.720 --> 16:19.850
I'm sorry. It's a visiting
Iranian ambassador with an emergency.

16:19.960 --> 16:23.165
Let's just stop pretending it's
effective to have a sex life.

16:23.240 --> 16:24.565
What?

16:24.640 --> 16:27.883
To schedule a night out, yeah?

16:35.480 --> 16:39.365
Do you need a ride somewhere
this morning, Mr. Grumpy Pants?

16:39.440 --> 16:42.005
- Yes.
- Where are you going?

16:42.080 --> 16:44.890
Upper West Side.

16:46.320 --> 16:47.845
Get dressed.

16:57.720 --> 16:59.165
Morning.

17:04.280 --> 17:08.204
I like the girl with the mob,
but I need some quotes about Iris.

17:08.280 --> 17:11.682
I'm going to reach out to her mother.
I'm going to try to track her down.

17:11.800 --> 17:13.962
- All right. Thanks, Bobby.
- Later.

17:14.040 --> 17:15.451
Yeah.

17:56.080 --> 17:57.969
Oh, God.

18:27.680 --> 18:29.325
Hello?

18:29.400 --> 18:31.685
Hey, it's Porter Wren.

18:31.760 --> 18:34.240
Well, hello, Porter Wren.

18:34.320 --> 18:35.525
How are you feeling?

18:35.600 --> 18:37.523
Did you roofie me last night?

18:37.600 --> 18:39.965
No, I didn't.

18:40.040 --> 18:42.168
Why are you calling me?

18:45.520 --> 18:48.410
"Opportunity only knocks once"?

18:55.640 --> 18:57.324
Hey.

18:57.400 --> 18:59.562
I just rode up the elevator
with Leonardo DiCaprio.

18:59.640 --> 19:02.041
Oh, yeah. He's got a friend upstairs.

19:02.160 --> 19:05.084
So, tell me how you met Simon.

19:05.160 --> 19:08.846
I was living a sort of tired,

19:08.960 --> 19:13.522
pretty girl, New York life,
you know? I had no money.

19:13.600 --> 19:18.125
I had given up on L.A.
after a year, and moved here.

19:18.200 --> 19:21.485
I was apartment-sitting for rich people,

19:21.560 --> 19:24.685
with no steady income or place to live.

19:24.760 --> 19:30.005
And I had just been fired for refusing
to date my asshole lawyer boss

19:30.080 --> 19:32.845
whose firm I was answering phones for.

19:32.920 --> 19:36.606
Did you have a laundry line hanging in
the backyard when you were growing up?

19:38.440 --> 19:39.521
Excuse me?

19:39.600 --> 19:42.485
You know, with jeans and t-shirts

19:42.560 --> 19:45.525
and underwear hanging in the backyard?

19:45.600 --> 19:47.090
A laundry line.

19:47.200 --> 19:49.441
Yeah, actually, I did.

19:49.520 --> 19:52.045
Me, too. I didn't like
my underwear hanging out there

19:52.120 --> 19:54.088
for the other kids to see,

19:54.200 --> 19:58.965
but I did enjoy my one friend's
mom's brassiere...

19:59.040 --> 20:02.681
- Right.
- ...hanging on their laundry line.

20:02.760 --> 20:07.483
He bought me a couple more drinks,
and we had an amazing conversation

20:07.600 --> 20:11.605
about our childhoods and parents.

20:13.360 --> 20:15.931
I knew who he was.
I recognized him right away.

20:17.880 --> 20:20.925
- He was very smart.
- Caroline.

20:21.000 --> 20:24.445
I'm going to ask you one, crazy question,

20:24.520 --> 20:26.405
but it's serious, not a joke.

20:26.480 --> 20:27.561
Okay.

20:28.720 --> 20:30.404
I want to marry you.

20:32.520 --> 20:35.485
Now, I know it sounds completely crazy,

20:35.560 --> 20:37.525
but I had just been sitting there thinking

20:37.600 --> 20:39.565
how I was probably going
to have to leave New York,

20:39.640 --> 20:44.362
and in walks this enigmatic, weird,

20:44.440 --> 20:45.771
brilliant human being.

20:48.080 --> 20:50.685
- Yes.
- Jesus. God.

20:50.760 --> 20:52.364
So, you met him in a bar.

20:52.480 --> 20:55.370
- Jesus.
- He proposed. You said yes.

20:55.480 --> 20:58.205
All within the span of less than an hour?

20:58.280 --> 21:00.485
Well, a few hours, but, yeah.

21:00.560 --> 21:01.561
Okay.

21:01.640 --> 21:03.085
I got a package from him the next day

21:03.160 --> 21:07.165
containing a flash drive
and an engagement ring.

21:08.440 --> 21:10.283
You want to see the video?

21:11.400 --> 21:12.447
Sure.

21:15.120 --> 21:16.645
Hey, Caroline.

21:16.720 --> 21:17.767
Hey.

21:19.520 --> 21:24.082
I've been thinking about you
since I left you earlier today.

21:24.160 --> 21:28.324
I was thinking about our, uh,
wedding vows and everything,

21:28.400 --> 21:32.883
and about how
the regular vows are, "I do,"

21:32.960 --> 21:35.122
and how that won't do, actually.

21:35.200 --> 21:38.965
So, I decided I want to make
my vows to you here, right now,

21:39.040 --> 21:41.405
this, this minute, exactly.

21:41.480 --> 21:43.642
And I have no idea what I'm going to say.

21:43.720 --> 21:45.563
But once it's done,
it'll be my vows to you, okay?

21:45.640 --> 21:47.605
So, after I said goodbye to you,

21:47.680 --> 21:51.002
I had dinner with, uh, Jessica Chastain.

21:51.120 --> 21:55.170
She wants to be in my next
movie, Strange Day.

21:56.600 --> 21:58.602
And she looks good.

21:58.680 --> 22:00.364
There was nothing wrong
with the conversation.

22:00.440 --> 22:04.684
She was very smart and funny,
and whatever,

22:04.800 --> 22:07.525
but she wasn't you, Caroline.

22:07.600 --> 22:11.207
I didn't get that "click" from her.

22:11.320 --> 22:13.766
I got the click from you.

22:15.160 --> 22:17.125
I got the click.

22:17.200 --> 22:21.243
When I was in high school, I got a job
as a busboy at this place in the Village,

22:21.360 --> 22:23.725
Dante's Café. But that was, uh,

22:23.800 --> 22:27.168
that was a big, big thing for me.

22:27.280 --> 22:31.602
I made some money and I got my first
camera, and I could watch all the people.

22:31.680 --> 22:34.923
There was this very beautiful
model who started coming in,

22:35.040 --> 22:37.645
her name was Ashley Montgomery.

22:37.720 --> 22:42.925
I would save her used cigarettes
with that perfect lipstick smudge,

22:43.000 --> 22:46.243
faintest trace of her perfume on them,

22:46.360 --> 22:48.405
and, when I got home,
I would lie naked in my bed

22:48.480 --> 22:52.685
and I would lay the cigarette
butts all over my body,

22:52.760 --> 22:56.321
even under my tongue, and even in
my ass, once, while I jerked off.

22:56.400 --> 22:58.004
I did not consider this strange.

22:58.080 --> 23:00.242
I'm sorry, is this still
his marriage proposal?

23:00.360 --> 23:03.364
- Yeah.
- I was certain that I would never...

23:03.440 --> 23:05.805
be loved, never.

23:05.880 --> 23:10.442
I swore that, if I ever had the
chance for somebody I loved,

23:10.520 --> 23:12.645
I would take it right away.
And when I saw you today,

23:12.720 --> 23:15.485
I saw a woman who could take it,
who could take me,

23:15.560 --> 23:18.404
who could fucking kick it back
at me, if she had to.

23:20.160 --> 23:23.482
This is my excitement...

23:25.520 --> 23:26.931
and my terror.

23:28.920 --> 23:32.129
My heart thrills to your heart, Caroline.

23:35.880 --> 23:38.087
My dark heart to your dark heart.

23:39.400 --> 23:43.200
That is my vow, Caroline, my vow to you.

23:43.280 --> 23:44.805
This is a song that makes me think of you.

23:49.560 --> 23:52.484
We were secretly married
in New York three days later.

23:53.800 --> 23:56.165
Showed a real affection for me.

23:56.240 --> 23:59.483
In the first six months, we were
surprisingly happy together.

23:59.560 --> 24:02.723
And this one night, when...

24:02.800 --> 24:07.124
when Simon didn't come
home, I got worried.

24:07.200 --> 24:11.330
But I didn't call the police because
I knew Simon would be pissed if I did.

